The paper deals with a problem related to constraint satisfaction and parameterized complexity, which are core topics in computer science. The use of kernels and user reductions is also a common technique in algorithm design and analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves some machine learning techniques, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of constraints, which could make it relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
